; Regression test for issue #1130: posting order should not affect -V conversion
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1130
;
; When a transaction has postings in two different commodities without
; explicit @ or @@ cost notation, ledger infers an exchange rate.  The
; order of postings within the transaction must not change which commodity
; is marked "primary" and thus whether -V converts it.

P 2015-08-07 00:00:00 GBP USD 2
P 2015-08-07 00:00:00 EUR USD 1.2

; Transaction 1: EUR purchase (EUR first)
2013-10-24 Default
    Assets:cash:eur      EUR 400.0
    Income:All      USD -420.0

; Transaction 2: EUR expense with reversed posting order
; (the source of the original bug -- swapping these two lines
; caused EUR to be incorrectly marked as COMMODITY_PRIMARY)
2013-10-24 Default
    Expenses:All      USD 210.0
    Assets:cash:eur      EUR -200.0

; Transaction 3: GBP purchase
2013-10-24 Default
    Assets:cash:gbp      GBP 300.0
    Income:All      USD -600.0

test bal -V assets
           USD 840.0  Assets:cash
           USD 240.0    eur
           USD 600.0    gbp
--------------------
           USD 840.0
end test

test bal -X USD assets
           USD 840.0  Assets:cash
           USD 240.0    eur
           USD 600.0    gbp
--------------------
           USD 840.0
end test
